         <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="discussion">
            <p>
Discussion.
When examining the 
<tp:taxon-name>
Homogryllacris
</tp:taxon-name>
specimens collected from 
Yunnan
, we discovered 
four specimens
sampled from Jinping, 
Yunnan
are very similar to 
<tp:taxon-name>
Homogryllacris yunnana
Shi, Guo &amp; Bian, 2012
</tp:taxon-name>
with regard to the posterior processes on male tenth abdominal tergite, but they differ from the latter in the following: posterior processes of male tenth abdominal tergite distinctly shorter, basal halves cylindrical, apical halves compressed, sickle-shaped, not decussate, apical areas slightly incurved, tips subacute. Furthermore, DNA sequencing was implemented in two of these 
four specimens
sampled from Jinping, 
Yunnan
and 
two specimens
of 
<tp:taxon-name>
Homogryllacris yunnana
Shi, Guo &amp; Bian, 2012
</tp:taxon-name>
sampled from Meizihu, Pu’er, 
Yunnan
based on 
COI
gene, respectively, the genetic distance between them is about 4.1%, which is far below the minimum value of interspecific genetic distances (The interspecific genetic distances range are 6.59–19.49% in the genus according to our analysis). As a consequence, with the consideration of morphological and molecular evidence, we regard these 
four specimens
sampled from Jinping, 
Yunnan
as a geographical population of 
<tp:taxon-name>
Homogryllacris yunnana
Shi, Guo &amp; Bian, 2012
</tp:taxon-name>
and the morphological difference mentioned above belongs to intraspecific variation.
</p>
