         <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="discussion">
            <p>
Discussion.
This species was originally described by Liu 
et al
. (2021) based on a male specimen (
holotype
: male, type locality: Gulinqing, Maguan, 
Yunnan
) and 
two female
specimens from the type locality. We examined specimens of the species from the type locality and 
one female
was identified as this species based on the shape of seventh abdominal sternite and subgenital plate, but 
two male
specimens are more similar to 
<tp:taxon-name>
Homogryllacris brevispina
Shi, Guo &amp; Bian, 2012
</tp:taxon-name>
with respect to male abdominal apex and differ from original description of 
<tp:taxon-name>
Homogryllacris platycis

Liu &amp; Bian, 
2021
</tp:taxon-name>
in the following: posterior processes on tenth abdominal tergite obviously longer, moderately incurved on the whole apart from basal areas, apical areas decussate and pointing outwards. Furthermore, according to results of molecular species delimitation in most species of 
<tp:taxon-name>
Homogryllacris
</tp:taxon-name>
based on 
COI
gene (unpublished), samples from Gulinqing, Maguan, 
Yunnan
and Yaoshan, Hekou, 
Yunnan
were assigned into a single molecular operational taxonomic unit (MOTU) in all five approaches. As a consequence, morphological difference of posterior processes on male tenth abdominal tergite is regarded as intraspecific variation.
</p>
